"{\"uid\": \"sbs.com.au-news-article-paris-olympics-day-14-1r8qbxguz\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Stream free online, anytime  Discover your world of SBS  Sign in or create an account  or  Stream free online, anytime  Get in touch:  Highlights around SBS:  Follow Us:  SBS acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of Country and their connections and continuous care for the skies, lands and waterways throughout Australia.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jessica Hull gave Australia its seventh track and field medal of the Paris Games.Source:AP/Matthias Schrader  Day 14 of the Paris Olympics was painted in silver as Jessica Hull got second place in the 1500m run and the Stingers loss to Spain in the women's water polo final.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Hull\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\"}, {\"begin\": 414, \"end\": 416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9996923101350512, \"rank\": 0.00030778456711714596, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 417, \"end\": 425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9124740057104045, \"rank\": 0.07594666607119746, \"text\": \"Matthias\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 490, \"end\": 502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Hull\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\"}, {\"begin\": 562, \"end\": 567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999999338863054, \"rank\": 6.547127369643161e-07, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two medals add to the Australian tally, which currently stands at 50: 18 gold, 18 silver and 14 bronze.\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 709, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 628, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999989425069677, \"rank\": 1.0377487969931262e-06, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jessica Hull has won Australia's first Olympic middle-distance medal in 56 years in magnificent style, pocketing the silver in three minutes 52.56 seconds - her second-fastest time ever.\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 711, \"end\": 723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Hull\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was only denied 1500m gold in Paris by Kenya's Faith Kipyegon, the greatest women's middle-distance runner of all-time.\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 1022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 933, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1981123831247112e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 942, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9980766469080253, \"rank\": 0.0019059665850654154, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 950, \"end\": 964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faith Kipyegon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kipyegon won in an Olympic record time of 3:51.29, adding a third successive Olympic 1500m title to her name.\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's Georgia took the bronze.\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9844237324571222, \"rank\": 0.015822725622389438, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"score\": 0.9998638193594516, \"rank\": 7.562233254339061e-05, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Australia's first Olympic middle-distance medal since Ralph Doubell won 800m gold in 1968 and the first time an Australian woman had pocketed an Olympic medal on the track at a distance further than 800m.\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1231, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Doubell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ralph Doubell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Doubell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Doubell\"}, {\"begin\": 1289, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999989425069677, \"rank\": 1.0377487969931262e-06, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's Stingers have suffered Olympic heartbreak, succumbing in the women's water polo final 11-9 to Spain as their frustrating 24-year wait for the biggest title in the sport goes on.\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1489, \"end\": 1494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999999338863054, \"rank\": 6.547127369643161e-07, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unbeaten throughout the tournament, history-making coach Bec Rippon's team finally met their match in a brilliant Spanish side at a throbbing La Defense Arena on Saturday.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_H._F._Rippon\", \"score\": 0.8805882913309449, \"rank\": 0.13560447000984527, \"text\": \"Rippon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_H._F._Rippon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_H._F._Rippon\"}, {\"begin\": 1688, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9858805782178439, \"rank\": 0.014279592375252687, \"text\": \"Spanish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not even five goals from their own brilliant top scorer Alice Williams was enough for the Stingers, who had been attempting to emulate the famous class of Sydney 2000, who won the inaugural women's tournament at home.\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1803, \"end\": 1817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Williams_(welfare)\", \"score\": 0.9999956317578746, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alice Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Williams_(welfare)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Williams_(welfare)\"}, {\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998767635, \"rank\": 1.2301445953447354e-10, \"text\": \"Sydney 2000\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxer Lin Yu-ting of Taiwan has won Olympic gold in the women's featherweight division following Imane Khelif's lead a day earlier with a glittering response to the intense scrutiny faced by both fighters over misconceptions about their womanhood.\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1972, \"end\": 1983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 1987, \"end\": 1993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.730365296981507, \"rank\": 0.26986419987891336, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 2063, \"end\": 2075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lin beat Julia Szeremeta of Poland 5-0 in the final at Roland Garros on Saturday night, capping her four-fight unbeaten run through Paris by ensuring Taiwan's first Olympic boxing medal is golden.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2224, \"end\": 2229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"score\": 0.998722825557219, \"rank\": 0.0012788024231951635, \"text\": \"Julia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\"}, {\"begin\": 2243, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999573228715, \"rank\": 4.1198468696270075e-08, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1981123831247112e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2365, \"end\": 2371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.730365296981507, \"rank\": 0.26986419987891336, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Friday,Khelif won Algeria's first women's boxing medalwith a decisive victory in her own final, beating Yang Liu of China.\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2434, \"end\": 2441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.8566269388606682, \"rank\": 0.16736931163183943, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 2520, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"score\": 0.9999966834675861, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yang Liu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\"}, {\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7515244184714486, \"rank\": 0.32396567472485904, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic champions Kaylee McKeown and Matt Wearn have been selected as Australia's closing ceremony flag bearers.\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2558, \"end\": 2572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeown successfully defended her individual 100m and 200m backstroke Olympic titles in Paris, becoming Australia's first four-time individual gold medallist, while Wearn won the men's dinghy sailing event, the first man to win back-to-back titles in this event in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2742, \"end\": 2747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1981123831247112e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pair will lead the Australian delegation, expected to include more than 300 athletes from 29 sports set to attend the Closing Ceremony in Stade de France.\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 3095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999989425069677, \"rank\": 1.0377487969931262e-06, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 3079, \"end\": 3094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hannah Green, Australia's world No.6 golfer, made a charge at Le Golf National, but just missed out on a medal by one shot, having to settle for a four-way tie for fourth place.\", \"from\": 3097, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3097, \"end\": 3109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Green_(golfer)\", \"score\": 0.9939553674195113, \"rank\": 0.006081081081082982, \"text\": \"Hannah Green\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Green_(golfer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Green_(golfer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fijian-born Aussie weightlifter Eileen Cikamatana was left in tears after a disappointing clean-and-jerk ensured she could only finish fourth in the 81kg class when she had been tipped for a medal.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3308, \"end\": 3325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Cikamatana\", \"score\": 0.9999980875591161, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eileen Cikamatana\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Cikamatana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Cikamatana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year's world diving champ Cassiel Rousseau just missed out on a medal in the 10m platform.\", \"from\": 3475, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassiel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cassiel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassiel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassiel\"}, {\"begin\": 3514, \"end\": 3522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Jacques_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999999996825863, \"rank\": 1.9486448260207615e-10, \"text\": \"Rousseau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Jacques_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Jacques_Rousseau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Olympic Committee president Thomas Bach announced he would not seek to stay in the post at the end of his second term next year, despite calls from members for him to keep going.\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3572, \"end\": 3603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3614, \"end\": 3625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3min read  Published11 August 20249:05am  Updated11 August 202411:24am  Source:AAP  Share this with family and friends  Sign up now for the latest news from Australia and around the world direct to your inbox.\", \"from\": 3766, \"to\": 3975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By subscribing, you agree to SBS'sterms of serviceandprivacy policyincluding receiving email updates from SBS.\", \"from\": 3979, \"to\": 4089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4085, \"end\": 4088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Broadcasting_Service\", \"score\": 0.9999999986830517, \"rank\": 1.3169364951457877e-09, \"text\": \"SBS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Broadcasting_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Broadcasting_Service\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the latest with ourNewspodcastson your favourite podcast apps.\", \"from\": 4091, \"to\": 4157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SBS World News  Take a global view with Australia's most comprehensive world news service  Watch now  Watch the latestnews videosfrom Australia and across the world  Locked Bag 028,Crows Nest NSW 1585  SBS acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of Country and their connections and continuous care for the skies, lands and waterways throughout Australia.\", \"from\": 4159, \"to\": 4514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4340, \"end\": 4350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crows_Nest_railway_station\", \"score\": 0.5033437218346634, \"rank\": 0.799655552038333, \"text\": \"Crows Nest\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crows_Nest_railway_station\", 